en_487610_0	New envoys have been appointed to Sri Lanka from four foreign countries.
en_487610_1	They have handed in their credentials to President Maithripala Sirisena.
en_487610_2	The new Ambassadors have been appointed from the United States, Japan, France and Afghanistan.
en_487610_3	New Ambassador from the United States Alaina Teplitz first presented her credentials to the President.
en_487610_4	She was followed by the new Ambassador from Japan Akira Sugiyama.
en_487610_5	New Ambassador of France to Sri Lanka Eric Lavertu handed over his credentials to the President.
en_487610_6	The new Ambassador of Afghanistan to Sri Lanka is Ashraf Haidari.
en_487610_7	He too handed over his credentials to the President.
en_487610_8	Foreign Minister Dr. Sarath Amunugama, Presidential Secretary Udaya R. Seneviratne and Foreign Secretary Ravinatha Ariyasinghe were present on the occasion.
